The paper deals with QoS-aware base station selection for distributed MIMO links in wireless networks, which involves optimization of resource allocation and transmission schemes. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers delay-QoS constraints and proposes techniques for probabilistic transmission, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper uses channel state information and QoS requirements to dynamically select a subset of base stations, which could involve machine learning or optimization techniques (cs.AI).
